-- Macklem Concerned With Canada’s Household Debt, Correio Says
-- B y   R a y m o n d   C o l i t t
-- 2012-03-14T13:54:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-14/macklem-concerned-with-canada-s-household-debt-correio-says.html
Canada ’s policy makers are
concerned with rising domestic  household debt  due to low
 interest rates , Central Bank Senior Deputy Governor Tiff Macklem
told Correio Braziliense.  “We’re alerting people not to take on debt they can’t
pay,” Macklem said in an interview with the newspaper today.  Like  Brazil , Canada also has an appreciated currency and
continues to attract foreign capital, Macklem said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Raymond Colitt in Brasilia Newsroom at 
 rcolitt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net  